#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:1
msgid "Add numpy support for composite arrays"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:3
msgid ""
"You can now use VTK composite arrays with numpy functionnality just like non "
"composite arrays. In terms of available features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:5
msgid ""
"All numpy related algorithms previously accessible via algs (alias for "
"numpy_interface.algorithms) are now accessible directly with their numpy "
"counterpart (algs.mean -> np.mean)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:6
msgid ""
"Most of in place numpy functions are now supported (typically math functions "
"like cos, arctan, ...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:7
msgid "Slicing is now available to extract specific elements or sub-arrays"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:8
msgid ""
"The old algs API is now deprecated for functions that have native NumPy "
"equivalents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:10
msgid ""
"Note that the algs intermediate layer is still useful to access some VTK "
"specific features, such as MPI related algs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:12
msgid "Developer notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:14
msgid ""
"NumPy supports extension of its core functionality to non-`ndarray` types "
"using two key protocols which were overriden in the `VTKCompositeDataArray` "
"class:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:15
msgid ""
"`__array_ufunc__`\\ This method is called whenever a NumPy universal "
"function (ufunc) like np.sin or np.sqrt is applied. Universal functions are "
"more or less the elementwise functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:0
msgid "<br />\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:0
msgid "\\\\\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-numpy-support-for-composite-arrays.md:17
msgid ""
"`__array_function__`\\ This method is used for non-ufunc NumPy functions, "
"such as np.mean or np.expand_dims. It is used for functions that imply "
"structural manipulation, and is thus more general than `__array_ufunc__`. We "
"register supported functions explicitly and dispatch to custom "
"implementations. The registration mechanism is handled by a simple "
"dictionnary and a function used as decorator."
msgstr ""
